\frac{d}{dt}(y-x) = 2 \implies y-x=2 t+C
\frac{d}{dt}(y+x) = 2 (x-y) = -4 t \implies y+x=-2 t^2 +C'
t^2+t+x=0 \implies t=-\frac12 \pm \frac12 \sqrt{1-4 x}
y=t-t^2+C = x-1\pm\sqrt{1-4 x}+C
x'=Dx, y'=Dy
